WEBVTT

00:08.042 --> 00:10.075
Oh! I just stopped
by to thank you

00:10.177 --> 00:13.412
for letting me borrow your
Daring Do books! I love them.

00:13.814 --> 00:16.982
Wait till you get to "Daring Do
and the Riddle of the Sphinx!"

00:17.084 --> 00:19.485
This is actually my
second time through!

00:19.587 --> 00:20.820
I've read them all,

00:20.922 --> 00:22.988
from "Daring Do and
the Sapphire Statue"

00:23.090 --> 00:25.657
to "Daring Do and the
Fallen Idol!"

00:25.759 --> 00:28.794
Fallen Idol? That's
not in the series.

00:28.896 --> 00:31.330
Oh, it just came
out last week...

00:31.432 --> 00:33.599
Maybe that's why you
haven't heard of it?

00:34.101 --> 00:38.237
No way Daring Do's
biggest fan, ME,

00:38.339 --> 00:39.805
would miss a
book coming out!

00:39.907 --> 00:43.275
Besides, A.K. Yearling
<i>always</i> sends me a copy!

00:43.677 --> 00:45.277
Well, I'm happy to
let you borrow mine

00:45.379 --> 00:46.946
until yours arrives.

00:47.448 --> 00:49.982
"The true story of
the thieving fraud

00:50.084 --> 00:52.384
known as Daring
Do?" WHAT?

00:52.486 --> 00:54.987
Why would A.K. Yearling
write that about herself!?

00:55.089 --> 00:57.289
Oh! It looks
like she didn't.

00:57.491 --> 01:01.593
This book says it's by
Groom Q. Q. Martingale.

01:01.695 --> 01:02.228
Who?

01:02.329 --> 01:03.962
I guess he's a
new writer.

01:05.866 --> 01:07.366
A BAD one.

01:07.468 --> 01:09.034
"The only thing worse
than Daring Do's

01:09.136 --> 01:10.637
destruction of temples

01:10.739 --> 01:14.506
is her cruelty to the
mild-mannered Dr. Caballeron!?"

01:14.608 --> 01:16.976
It <i>was</i> written from
his point of view...

01:17.078 --> 01:19.712
I figured it was
an artistic choice.

01:20.114 --> 01:21.647
More like a disaster!

01:21.749 --> 01:24.783
Listen: "Daring Do isn't
just a fictional character

01:24.885 --> 01:26.819
from over-the-top
adventure stories.

01:26.921 --> 01:30.790
I've met her, and she
is a real, live pony!"

01:30.892 --> 01:32.491
That's supposed
to be a secret!

01:33.744 --> 01:35.794
We're the only ones
who know Daring Do

01:35.896 --> 01:38.197
is really A.K.
Yearling in disguise.

01:38.299 --> 01:40.099
But if other ponies
read this book,

01:40.201 --> 01:42.401
how long will it take
them to figure that out?

01:42.503 --> 01:43.969
We have to go
warn her!

01:44.371 --> 01:45.638
FLUTTERSHY!

01:46.540 --> 01:48.006
Hmm? Oh. Sorry.

02:27.981 --> 02:29.548
A.K. Yearling is
signing all her books

02:29.650 --> 02:30.749
at the bookstore today.

02:30.851 --> 02:32.684
We can warn her about
what's going on!

02:32.786 --> 02:36.087
Don't you think you should
read Martingale's book first?

02:36.189 --> 02:38.290
Just to hear both
sides of the story?

02:38.392 --> 02:41.993
Uh, why? The only true
thing in that pack of LIES

02:42.095 --> 02:43.962
is that Daring Do is REAL.

02:44.064 --> 02:45.464
There's also a
lot of insight

02:45.566 --> 02:48.199
into Dr. Caballeron's
life choices.

02:48.301 --> 02:50.535
Did you know he's actually
a history professor

02:50.637 --> 02:52.671
and amateur bird watcher?

02:52.773 --> 02:54.539
Are you serious
right now!?

02:54.741 --> 02:58.710
A random writer TRASHES our
friend and exposes her secret

02:59.012 --> 03:01.280
and you wanna
talk ABOUT BIRDS!?

03:01.682 --> 03:03.649
[whispering] Also spider cruelty.

03:03.951 --> 03:04.816
WHAT?

03:05.118 --> 03:06.785
You have to
admit Daring Do

03:06.887 --> 03:09.821
wrecks a lot of spider
webs in her adventures.

03:09.923 --> 03:13.592
<i>In order</i> to save precious
artifacts from the bad guy,

03:13.694 --> 03:16.728
who you seem to have
forgotten is Dr. Caballeron!

03:16.830 --> 03:18.797
Are you sure you read
the same series I did?

03:20.100 --> 03:22.601
♪♪

03:22.703 --> 03:25.470
Well, at least A.K.
Yearling's TRUE fans

03:25.572 --> 03:27.906
know Martingale's
book is bogus.

03:28.308 --> 03:31.276
I'm not sure those
are all fans...

03:31.378 --> 03:34.546
♪♪

03:34.648 --> 03:37.215
Why didn't your books
say Daring Do was real!?

03:37.317 --> 03:38.950
This changes everything!

03:39.052 --> 03:41.787
And why do you only write
about her good side?

03:41.889 --> 03:43.388
Is she bribing you?

03:43.490 --> 03:46.758
On page 531 it says
Daring Do kicks puppies!

03:46.860 --> 03:48.077
She does!?

03:48.178 --> 03:50.895
What!? No! Look,
are any of you here

03:50.997 --> 03:52.731
for my actual
book signing?

03:53.333 --> 03:55.467
Nuh-uh. No.

03:55.569 --> 03:58.970
Uh-uh. Frankly, I don't even know
how you can call it <i>fiction</i>

03:59.072 --> 04:02.607
if it's all real. You're as
much of a fake as Daring Do!

04:05.679 --> 04:07.979
Uh.. I guess we're a little
late to warn you

04:08.081 --> 04:09.681
about the new book, huh?

04:10.484 --> 04:12.751
[sigh] I always feared
that someday

04:12.853 --> 04:15.654
everypony would learn
Daring Do was real.

04:15.756 --> 04:18.623
But why? Aren't you
proud of your adventures?

04:18.725 --> 04:21.493
Of course! But I'm not
in it for the fame.

04:21.595 --> 04:24.863
The stories just seemed
too good to keep to myself.

04:25.265 --> 04:28.533
I wish I knew who this
"Martingale" author was,

04:28.635 --> 04:32.471
and why he's determined to
ruin my character... and me!

04:32.573 --> 04:34.106
Maybe we can ask him.

04:34.908 --> 04:38.443
No way! He's doing a
signing across the street!?

04:38.645 --> 04:40.078
You'd better
go without me.

04:40.180 --> 04:42.147
I can't risk the
chance Martingale

04:42.249 --> 04:44.382
might recognize
me as Daring Do.

04:44.484 --> 04:48.887
♪♪

04:48.989 --> 04:51.956
Oops! Um, sorry.
Excuse us!

04:55.496 --> 04:57.929
[gasp] That's not Martingale!

04:58.031 --> 05:00.399
It's Doctor Caballeron
in disguise!

05:00.501 --> 05:03.368
Now it all makes sense!
Daring Do's arch nemesis

05:03.470 --> 05:06.338
created a fake "author"
self so he can write books

05:06.440 --> 05:09.074
that make him sound like
a hero! Who does that!?

05:09.176 --> 05:11.176
Uh, A.K. Yearling?

05:11.278 --> 05:12.277
This is totally
different.

05:13.279 --> 05:17.048
Well, well, well. Up to
your old tricks again, huh?

05:17.150 --> 05:18.650
Just like in Somnambula!

05:18.752 --> 05:21.453
Spreading lies to make
Daring Do look bad!

05:21.555 --> 05:22.754
Would you sign our book?

05:22.856 --> 05:27.559
I am just a simple author,
telling it like it is.

05:27.661 --> 05:30.028
Who should I make
it out to?

05:31.031 --> 05:32.764
Fluttershy, with two T's.

05:33.267 --> 05:35.267
Agh! We know who you
REALLY are!

05:35.369 --> 05:37.402
And unless you want us
to tell all of THEM,

05:37.504 --> 05:39.438
you'd better answer
some questions!

05:39.740 --> 05:42.974
I'm afraid that's all
we have time for today.

05:43.076 --> 05:44.260
Awwww!

05:44.361 --> 05:47.945
But please! Take a free copy
of my book on your way out!

05:48.048 --> 05:48.980
Yeah!

05:54.721 --> 05:57.455
We aren't going to let you get
away with this, Caballeron!

05:57.557 --> 06:02.627
Get away with what? I am merely
telling my side of the story.

06:02.729 --> 06:04.062
You mean lying!

06:04.164 --> 06:06.831
You think everything in A.K.
Yearling's books are true?

06:06.933 --> 06:08.700
In "Daring Do and
the Quetzal's Quest"

06:08.802 --> 06:11.836
she states that the
Fangthorn Flowers are red.

06:11.938 --> 06:14.473
In fact, they are blue!

06:14.675 --> 06:16.375
It's true. They are.

06:17.077 --> 06:20.145
Pfft! That sounds like more
of an editor's mistake.

06:20.247 --> 06:22.013
Still, if that is wrong...

06:22.115 --> 06:25.116
is it not possible that
other, bigger things are too?

06:25.218 --> 06:26.618
Take a look! It's
in my book.

06:27.020 --> 06:29.654
But I don't have to
take YOUR word for it!

06:29.956 --> 06:31.189
C'mon, Fluttershy!

06:32.759 --> 06:34.092
Is something wrong?

06:34.294 --> 06:36.995
It is terrible being
misunderstood.

06:37.097 --> 06:40.031
It is true, in the past
I have not been as nice

06:40.133 --> 06:44.569
to Daring Do as I should.
But I have my reasons!

06:44.771 --> 06:46.605
Want to talk about
what happened?

06:47.207 --> 06:49.207
My team and I were
only ever interested

06:49.309 --> 06:51.276
in researching
artifacts.

06:51.378 --> 06:52.711
And taking them
to our museum

06:52.813 --> 06:55.179
<i> where other ponies</i>
<i> could study them.</i>

06:55.281 --> 06:58.316
♪♪

06:58.418 --> 07:01.252
<i> But Daring Do always</i>
<i> seemed to get there first,</i>

07:01.354 --> 07:02.788
<i> with her own plans.</i>

07:03.490 --> 07:06.524
<i> I offered to team up with</i>
<i> her, but she refused.</i>

07:08.295 --> 07:11.897
<i> She had her own ideas of</i>
<i> where the treasures belonged.</i>

07:12.199 --> 07:14.165
Daring Do <i>did</i> have
a lot of artifacts

07:14.267 --> 07:15.567
on her shelves at home...

07:15.869 --> 07:18.637
But didn't <i>you</i> try to sell
them to the highest bidder?

07:18.739 --> 07:20.305
Only because I
had to.

07:20.407 --> 07:23.341
<i> Since Daring Do kept</i>
<i> taking our artifacts,</i>

07:23.443 --> 07:25.244
<i> our museum closed!</i>

07:25.546 --> 07:28.647
<i> We were desperate for</i>
<i> money to keep it open.</i>

07:33.921 --> 07:37.188
She <i>does</i> destroy a
lot of ancient sites..

07:37.290 --> 07:40.425
Not to mention the homes of
the animals that live there.

07:40.527 --> 07:43.495
And I felt it was MY
duty to tell the world.

07:43.597 --> 07:47.898
Thank you for listening
and understanding, Ms...?

07:48.235 --> 07:50.001
Fluttershy. Two T's.

07:50.303 --> 07:53.338
And I am Dr.
Caballeron.

07:53.440 --> 07:56.708
Martingale is merely a nom
de plume to build my brand.

07:56.910 --> 08:00.478
You know, my team could
use an insightful Pegasus

08:00.580 --> 08:02.247
like you, Fluttershy.

08:02.349 --> 08:05.917
Have you ever thought
of being.. an adventurer?

08:06.119 --> 08:07.219
Who, me?

08:08.321 --> 08:10.889
♪♪

08:11.925 --> 08:14.259
Finally! What
took you so long?

08:14.461 --> 08:16.227
I decided to find
out which author

08:16.329 --> 08:18.129
is <i>really</i> telling
the truth,

08:18.231 --> 08:21.766
so I joined Dr. C's
Tenochtitlan expedition!

08:21.868 --> 08:24.102
<i> ♪ [ominous music] ♪</i>

08:24.204 --> 08:26.804
Say <i>WHAAAT?</i>

08:31.078 --> 08:33.045
So Daring Do doesn't
kick puppies?

08:33.347 --> 08:36.248
That was ONE time.
Accidentally!

08:36.550 --> 08:38.250
A.K.! You have to help me!

08:38.652 --> 08:41.252
Groom Q.Q. Martingale is
really Dr. Caballeron,

08:41.354 --> 08:43.021
and he has Fluttershy!

08:43.423 --> 08:44.656
The book thing was
his new plan

08:44.758 --> 08:46.324
to ruin Daring
Do's reputation.

08:46.426 --> 08:48.693
AND he's trying to make
my friend a criminal!

08:48.795 --> 08:50.829
They're off to
Tenochtitlan right now!

08:51.431 --> 08:54.833
He must be after the Truth
Talisman of Tonatiuh!

08:54.935 --> 08:57.969
It requires the wings of
a Pegasus to retrieve it!

08:58.071 --> 09:00.305
That's gotta be why
Caballeron tricked Fluttershy

09:00.407 --> 09:01.973
into joining his gang!

09:02.275 --> 09:04.509
Then it's up to
us to stop him!

09:07.080 --> 09:08.747
Whoa...!

09:08.850 --> 09:17.818
♪♪

09:17.958 --> 09:20.258
Watch where you put
your hooves, everypony.

09:20.460 --> 09:24.463
We do not want to disturb the
fragile jungle ecosystem.

09:24.665 --> 09:27.065
Oh, that's so thoughtful.

09:27.167 --> 09:31.002
Yes, unlike Daring Do,
who slashes plants aside

09:31.104 --> 09:32.770
with her cruel machete.

09:33.573 --> 09:34.506
Thank you.

09:36.510 --> 09:39.144
Fool! Don't you
know that's poison?

09:40.346 --> 09:44.649
I don't want you to get
hurt, my friend. Heh heh.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.251
But I'm hungry.

09:46.653 --> 09:49.621
Oh, I can help
with that! Here!

09:49.923 --> 09:52.857
You are...willing
to share?

09:52.959 --> 09:55.159
Of course! That's
part of the fun

09:55.261 --> 09:57.228
of having an adventure
with friends!

10:09.376 --> 10:11.243
<i> ♪ [tense music] ♪</i>

10:11.345 --> 10:14.312
♪♪

10:14.514 --> 10:16.481
Fluttershy! Run!

10:16.583 --> 10:19.384
These ferocious beasts
want to eat us for dinner!

10:19.486 --> 10:21.386
That's a common
misconception.

10:21.488 --> 10:23.455
Have you ever tried
just talking to them?

10:23.657 --> 10:26.391
That's crazy! You
are on your own!

10:27.427 --> 10:28.527
She's a goner.

10:28.729 --> 10:29.961
I can't watch!

10:32.433 --> 10:35.166
We're very sorry for
coming into your territory.

10:35.468 --> 10:37.001
But we're just
passing through.

10:37.103 --> 10:39.337
How...did you do that?

10:39.439 --> 10:41.806
Everycreature likes
to be listened to.

10:41.908 --> 10:44.609
You just need to take the
time to understand them.

10:44.711 --> 10:48.046
You are more talented
than I realized..

10:48.148 --> 10:51.482
Thanks. I'm having the
best time with you all!

10:52.519 --> 10:54.319
Fluttershy must be
having the WORST time

10:54.421 --> 10:56.020
with Caballeron's goons.

10:56.122 --> 10:57.388
We need to catch
up to them

10:57.490 --> 10:59.591
before they reach
the truth talisman!

10:59.793 --> 11:01.860
Why? What's so
special about it?

11:01.962 --> 11:04.629
It has the power to
make the pony holding it

11:04.731 --> 11:05.764
tell the truth.

11:05.866 --> 11:07.532
But Caballeron only
wants it because

11:07.634 --> 11:09.300
it's made of
solid gold.

11:09.402 --> 11:11.903
He'll melt it down and
use it to get rich.

11:12.005 --> 11:14.072
So if this talisman
is so important,

11:14.174 --> 11:15.840
why didn't you
already save it?

11:15.942 --> 11:18.076
You said only a Pegasus
can get it, right?

11:18.178 --> 11:20.945
Yes! But the temple traps
are far too dangerous

11:21.047 --> 11:24.215
to face without a map.
And maybe even <i>with</i> one!

11:27.354 --> 11:30.421
<i> ♪ [military snare drum] ♪</i>

11:30.523 --> 11:32.924
Boss, how about we
take the shortcut?

11:33.026 --> 11:34.359
How about you
be quiet!

11:35.429 --> 11:37.462
Uh, I mean... no
thank you, Biff.

11:37.564 --> 11:39.197
Let's just
follow the map.

11:39.699 --> 11:43.034
Aw. I'm supposed to be Dr.
C's second in command.

11:43.136 --> 11:44.736
But he never
listens to me.

11:45.238 --> 11:48.073
Well, keep trying!
I believe in you.

11:48.175 --> 11:52.477
♪♪

11:52.579 --> 11:53.946
At last!

11:54.748 --> 11:57.215
Now we simply have to
wait for the sun

11:57.317 --> 11:59.250
to reach its
highest point.

12:00.754 --> 12:03.088
And our path will
be revealed.

12:03.190 --> 12:07.659
♪♪

12:07.761 --> 12:10.128
Withers. Don't. Move.

12:21.374 --> 12:22.774
Ah ha ha!

12:24.544 --> 12:25.577
There they are!

12:25.679 --> 12:27.878
We can catch them before
they enter the temple!

12:29.482 --> 12:30.148
Gah!

12:31.817 --> 12:34.552
Get back, Rainbow
Dash! It's Ahuizotl-

12:35.422 --> 12:36.354
Wha? Gah!

12:38.458 --> 12:41.826
Daring Do. My old nemesis.

12:42.028 --> 12:44.796
You may have outsmarted
my jungle cats,

12:44.898 --> 12:47.298
but you cannot escape ME!

12:47.668 --> 12:50.735
Ugh! We didn't see any cats!

12:51.037 --> 12:53.071
We're just here to
rescue Fluttershy!

12:54.841 --> 12:59.043
Hmm. It must be a coincidence
that only a Pegasus

12:59.145 --> 13:01.346
can retrieve
Tonatiuh's treasure...

13:01.548 --> 13:04.482
And there are
two of you here.

13:05.685 --> 13:09.854
♪♪

13:11.858 --> 13:19.426
♪♪

13:22.368 --> 13:24.869
<i> ♪ [adventurous music] ♪</i>

13:24.971 --> 13:26.404
♪♪

13:32.579 --> 13:35.213
Quickly! Before the sun
moves and it closes!

13:35.315 --> 13:44.083
♪♪

13:44.491 --> 13:47.258
Phew! <i>That</i> was
cutting it close.

13:47.660 --> 13:50.962
And without a map, we'll have
to guess which way to go.

13:58.605 --> 14:01.806
Oh, no! I knew
the truth talisman

14:01.908 --> 14:05.777
could not be moved by
magic, but I never realized

14:05.879 --> 14:08.913
we'd have to FLY
to retrieve it!

14:09.015 --> 14:12.417
Our journey has
been for nothing!

14:12.719 --> 14:14.853
Don't be upset,
I can get it.

14:15.055 --> 14:17.322
Oh, Fluttershy,
you are too kind.

14:17.424 --> 14:22.427
But I could never ask that of
you. It might be dangerous..!

14:22.529 --> 14:26.497
I want to do it! For all
of you, my new friends.

14:26.599 --> 14:28.966
And to protect a
historical treasure!

14:34.407 --> 14:38.042
♪♪

14:38.144 --> 14:39.644
Give me a hoof here!

14:52.358 --> 14:57.095
<i> ♪ [dark music] ♪</i>

15:02.302 --> 15:03.768
We did it!

15:03.870 --> 15:05.203
You're safe!

15:05.405 --> 15:06.737
Thanks, everypony.

15:06.861 --> 15:10.461
♪♪

15:10.543 --> 15:12.877
Give us the talisman,
Caballeron!

15:12.979 --> 15:15.346
We're not taking
no for an answer!

15:15.448 --> 15:19.183
Wait! You don't understand.
My friends are researchers!

15:19.285 --> 15:20.851
They only want to
study the talisman

15:20.953 --> 15:24.289
and keep it safe in a
museum! Right, Dr. C?

15:24.391 --> 15:26.057
Uh... no.

15:26.359 --> 15:28.026
Ah! But... but...you said...

15:28.128 --> 15:30.528
Now that he's holding
Tonatiuh's talisman,

15:30.630 --> 15:32.097
he has to tell the truth!

15:32.499 --> 15:34.232
Admit it,
Caballeron!

15:34.334 --> 15:36.134
You're only pretending
to like Fluttershy

15:36.236 --> 15:37.669
because she has the
wings you needed

15:37.771 --> 15:39.637
to steal the
truth talisman!

15:39.739 --> 15:40.872
Isn't that
right?

15:41.074 --> 15:41.806
No!

15:42.008 --> 15:44.309
I admit, that was
the original reason.

15:44.411 --> 15:46.978
But my henchponies and
I have come to value

15:47.080 --> 15:48.746
your friendship
and kindness.

15:49.783 --> 15:50.915
Didn't see that
coming.

15:52.652 --> 15:53.718
Or that!

15:54.220 --> 16:00.191
More intruders!? And you DARE
to steal Tonatiuh's talisman!?

16:00.293 --> 16:03.428
Guardian-goyles, ATTACK!

16:17.888 --> 16:19.888
♪♪

16:20.013 --> 16:24.482
Fluttershy! Can't you ask them
to stop, like the jungle cats!?

16:24.884 --> 16:28.252
Um, excuse me?
Uh, Guardian-goyles?

16:29.889 --> 16:33.324
It's no good! They're only
stone and magic, not alive.

16:33.426 --> 16:35.693
I encountered some
like this in Marapore.

16:35.795 --> 16:38.295
Ah, yes. I seem to
recall similar creations

16:38.397 --> 16:39.730
in Flankladesh.

16:40.032 --> 16:42.167
So..? How do you
get rid of them!?

16:44.037 --> 16:46.404
I know they don't
like bright light!

16:46.606 --> 16:48.139
There's none of
that in here.

16:48.441 --> 16:50.474
Not yet... Caballeron!

16:50.576 --> 16:53.010
Do you still have the
Diamond of Lapis-Lux?

16:53.112 --> 16:58.016
Yes. I mean, YES.
I mean... Argh!

16:58.518 --> 17:00.785
How did you know
<i>I</i> stole it?

17:00.887 --> 17:02.887
Lucky guess.
Hold it high!

17:02.989 --> 17:11.755
<i> ♪ [heroic music] ♪</i>

17:11.898 --> 17:14.698
Wow! You two make
a great team!

17:14.800 --> 17:16.967
Yeah, I'm not sure
how I feel about that.

17:17.069 --> 17:19.637
Feel later! Now,
it's time to escape!

17:21.073 --> 17:22.306
If we want to get
out of here,

17:22.408 --> 17:24.275
we're all gonna have
to work TOGETHER.

17:24.377 --> 17:27.678
That's...er actually
a good idea.

17:27.980 --> 17:30.147
See? Told you he'd listen.

17:30.249 --> 17:33.651
A truce until we escape?
But how can we trust you?

17:33.753 --> 17:36.720
I cannot lie. Now,
all together!

17:43.830 --> 17:45.796
Ah! You again!?

17:49.736 --> 17:51.702
If I wanted to
play GAMES,

17:51.804 --> 17:54.071
I would get out
my pinochle deck!

17:57.477 --> 17:58.376
This way!

17:58.478 --> 18:03.314
♪♪

18:03.416 --> 18:04.482
Rainbow Dash!

18:04.584 --> 18:06.417
♪♪

18:06.519 --> 18:09.687
I'm gonna need the deluxe spa
package after <i>this</i> adventure.

18:09.789 --> 18:11.222
That doesn't leave
this temple!

18:11.624 --> 18:21.392
♪♪

18:21.567 --> 18:24.368
That's it! I'm quitting
the henchpony business

18:24.470 --> 18:28.639
to finally follow my dreams
of becoming an opera star!

18:29.676 --> 18:32.009
Uh...maybe you
should hold this.

18:33.013 --> 18:37.448
You cannot hide in there
forever! It's a DEAD end.

18:37.650 --> 18:39.550
Ha ha ha ha!

18:42.588 --> 18:45.155
Ahuizotl won't give up
until he catches us!

18:46.593 --> 18:49.394
I think our problem
is the solution.

18:49.596 --> 18:51.629
Uh, did you forget there's
a monster out there

18:51.731 --> 18:52.897
that wants to crush us?

18:53.199 --> 18:56.033
But WHY? Nopony
ever asked Ahuizotl

18:56.135 --> 18:58.036
what <i>his</i> side of
the story is.

18:58.138 --> 19:00.572
He must have a reason
for being so upset.

19:01.074 --> 19:04.042
Or <i>maybe</i> he's
just a bad guy!

19:04.144 --> 19:06.644
Do I need to remind you he
tried to squash Daring Do

19:06.746 --> 19:07.945
like a hundred times!?

19:08.781 --> 19:10.481
And me as well.
I was so scared,

19:10.583 --> 19:15.019
I had to change my ascot.
Ah! Curse this truth teller!

19:15.921 --> 19:18.489
Understanding begins
with listening.

19:22.462 --> 19:25.396
Prepared to
meet your DOOM!?

19:25.798 --> 19:28.899
Um, not really.
Just here to ask...

19:29.001 --> 19:31.602
Why are you chasing
us, Mr. Ahuizotl?

19:33.940 --> 19:35.973
Well, the thing is,

19:36.175 --> 19:38.776
I'm in charge of
protecting this jungle.

19:38.878 --> 19:41.946
If another artifact goes
missing on my watch,

19:42.048 --> 19:44.548
I'm going to be
in SO much trouble

19:44.650 --> 19:46.817
with the other
guardian creatures.

19:46.919 --> 19:50.555
Oh! That sounds like a
lot of responsibility...

19:50.657 --> 19:56.627
Wha--! It is! And those two have taken
so many relics from my land,

19:56.729 --> 19:58.463
my job is on the line!

19:58.765 --> 20:03.200
So maybe I am a little
violent and ferocious..

20:03.502 --> 20:04.802
Can you blame me?

20:10.443 --> 20:12.343
The only reason I've
been taking the artifacts

20:12.445 --> 20:14.779
is because I <i>thought</i>
I was protecting them.

20:15.081 --> 20:17.048
I was stealing
them to get rich!

20:17.450 --> 20:21.152
Uh.. But I never realized
you had a noble cause!

20:21.354 --> 20:23.554
I thought you were
just being a monster.

20:24.991 --> 20:26.223
I get that a lot.

20:26.325 --> 20:28.025
Maybe there is
something to this

20:28.127 --> 20:30.528
whole "listening to
everypony" thing.

20:30.830 --> 20:33.030
It doesn't always mean
they're telling the truth,

20:33.132 --> 20:35.900
but everycreature
deserves kindness.

20:36.202 --> 20:39.503
True. And because you
returned the talisman

20:39.605 --> 20:42.407
and took the time
to understand me,

20:43.209 --> 20:45.743
I will let you all go.

20:50.382 --> 20:52.017
On one condition!

20:52.919 --> 20:55.886
You swear to never
steal artifacts

20:55.988 --> 20:59.023
from the Tenochtitlan
basin again!

21:00.659 --> 21:02.293
I promise!

21:02.595 --> 21:04.428
I'll even write that
in my next book.

21:04.730 --> 21:06.430
YOUR next book?

21:06.532 --> 21:09.033
You mean you're
actually A.K. Yearling!?

21:09.135 --> 21:10.568
Don't tell anypony!

21:10.970 --> 21:13.137
That gives me an idea..

21:14.574 --> 21:16.306
Hey! What's going on?

21:16.408 --> 21:18.008
I thought your first
co-written novel

21:18.110 --> 21:19.943
would bring out
a ton of fans!

21:20.745 --> 21:23.214
We've been upstaged
by a new author.

21:24.817 --> 21:29.787
And so the noble Ahuizotl
bravely toiled day and night

21:29.889 --> 21:32.556
to protect the jungle's
precious artifacts...
